Next stop Aconcagua! 🏔️⁣
⁣

Ready to get going! We leave for day one of trekking this morning! 🏔️⁣
⁣
The landscape is incredible and the team is in great form! ⁣
⁣
It will take us three days to reach base camp & we won’t have any contact again until then! Once we reach base camp we will have a rest day and some time to recover! ⁣
⁣
It’s going to be an epic few weeks! @earths_edge 
⁣
#Aconcagua

Greetings from Basecamp! We arrived in yesterday afternoon after a three day trek through the Vacas Valley! The views & landscape were spectacular! 👌🏻⁣
⁣
Today is a full rest day and we’re preparing kit and food for higher up the mountain! Tomorrow morning we’re taking a load up to Camp One before returning to basecamp then again! ⁣
⁣
The weathers been kind to us and the team are doing great! The longer range weather looks good so fingers crossed for a good end to the week! ⁣
⁣
Will check in again before we leave! 🏔️⁣
⁣
@earths_edge 
⁣
#Aconcagua

social_posts.post_text:
Our final rest day at Basecamp! Yesterday we did a load carry up to camp one which is at 5000 meters & tomorrow we move up there fully!⁣
⁣
The team is in great spirits and everyone is feeling well! 🏔️⁣
⁣
The rest of today will be all about taking it easy & prepping our final bits of kit for higher up the mountain! ⁣
⁣
@earths_edge 
@reviveactive 
@eatallreal 
⁣
#Aconcagua ⁣

Aconcagua Summit - Wednesday February 15th! 
⁣
What an adventure! Hard to start putting the whole trip into words yet, but around lunch time on Wednesday we summited what I can only say is an incredible mountain!⁣ 🏔️
⁣
The 3:30am wake up call was made worthwhile after the hard few weeks of getting to Camp 3! ⁣
⁣
Our team and guides were incredible and as @jammcmanus said it was really cool to see everyone pull together and support each other all the way!⁣
⁣
Conditions on the mountain were challenging during our trip but also over the last few weeks & we got a really good run of weather which allowed us to give it a good go!⁣
⁣
More updates and photos to come but for now it’s showers, real food and a change of clothes 😂⁣
⁣
@earths_edge 
⁣
#Aconcagua ⁣

Exciting News! We are heading back to Kilimanjaro & Tanzania in January 2024!! 

Very excited to have this expedition to look forward to & I can’t wait to climb Kilimanjaro again with another group of great people!

The aim of this Kilimanjaro Expedition is to raise funds & awareness for the @tirnanogchildrensfoundation in Tanzania.

Tír na nÓg Children's Foundation was established in 2007 by Tralee woman Louise Quill to alleviate the suffering of Tanzanian children and to provide a home where they would be nurtured in a loving, safe environment. Their aim is to ‘change one child’s life at a time’ by educating children according to their abilities and developing schools to create the leaders of tomorrow.

The Tír na nÓg children’s village is home to over 60 children in Boma village at the foot of Kilimanjaro. The entire project will be self-sufficient with power generated using solar and water pumped from an on-site borehole. All waste is treated through a constructed wetland reed bed system which will deliver clean water to be used for irrigation for growing agricultural crops, fruit trees and bushes on site. For more information visit
www.tirnanogchildrensfoundation.com

This expedition has been set up with a very specific goal; To support the construction of a computer lab at the village. We are looking for 25 people to raise at least €2,000 each, so that we can collectively raise the €50,000 required to construct the computer lab. Teaching the children computer skills will have a transformative impact on their prospects of joining third-level education and gaining skilled work thereafter. 

Upon signing up for this expedition Tír na nÓg will be in touch with you with fundraising advice and support. There will be an opportunity to visit the village on Day 11 of the expedition.

If you have had Kilimanjaro on your bucket list - now is your time to join us! We provide you with all the training and support that you need in order to have a successful trip! Places are available on a first come first served basis! Any questions please let me know!

Link in bio to reserve your place!

After lots of planning, chatting and manifesting we are delighted to finally launch our Outwest Outdoor Club - a new platform for our community of like-minded people, who want to immerse themselves in nature, the outdoors and the local community ⛰️

We’re kicking things off this Saturday at 9am from our Outwest Shop in Dingle! @outwestireland 

The Outwest Outdoor Club is open to everyone & our goal is to get more people into the outdoors, exploring their local landscapes and making adventure part of their life! 🌎

We welcome locals, tourists & visitors to join us on our weekly adventures. Many of these adventures will be free to attend so we recommend pre-booking in advance to secure your place! So if you plan on visiting the Dingle Peninsula at any point moving forward be sure to join us - we’d love to have you! 👌🏻
